odemis (3.2.0-1) bionic; urgency=medium

  * New version: 3.2
  * Main new changes and features:
    - Colourmap option for streams in the GUI
    - Support for the METEOR systems
    - Support for the ENZEL systems
    - Support for the FASTEM systems
    - Add EK (Angular Spectrum) acquisition support for the SPARC
    - Support for Thermofisher SEM
    - Support for Ubuntu 20.04
    - Only Ubuntu 18.04 and later is supported
    - Only Python 3.6 and later is supported
  * Other improvements and bug fixes:
    - Option to control digital SEM external/blanker when analog scan is used
    - Support for hardware trigger on Andor SDK2 cameras
    - Support for SmarAct Picoscale interferometers
    - Support for SmarAct SmarPod actuators
    - Support for Piezomotors actuators
    - Support for Picoquant HydraHarp 400
    - Addition of the !include and !extend tags to merge yaml files
    - odemis-cli is now called odemis
    - Updated instructions to use Odemis with Anaconda on Windows
    - fix discontinuity in AR projection around phi=0
  * Improvements and bug fixes already present in the v3.1 branch:
    - Fix bug reporter sometimes not showing a confirmation of the reception
    - Bug reporter can be internally set to send to a different department
    - New image in Windows installer
    - When "show pixel value" is selected, the value under the cursor is
      immediately shown.
    - merge_RGB plugin detects that the pixel size read in the TIFF is 
      too large and replaces it by a fallback sane value.
    - Andorcam 3: improve temperature control
    - Andorcam 3: fix large horizontal binning not working
    - Andorcam 3: support for Sona cameras
    - New "AR to CSV" script, to export AR from the command line.
    - Odemis Viewer now 64 bits
    - Smaller Odemis Viewer installer
    - When "show pixel value" is selected, it's now possible to change
      focus, use measure tool, etc.
    - On Windows, when exporting CSV files, they would sometimes have an extra line
    - Fix download of new version from the Windows Viewer
    - Restore the "snapshot" screen feedback
    - When exporting to CSV, AR polarimetry samples acquired with drift correction,
      it could sometimes fail.
    - Warn if the user is trying to open AR polarimetry data, without having
      the special polarimetry module
    - If a move fails on a Physik Instrumente actuator, properly report it
      in the GUI
    - Do not restart the GUI when odemis icon is pressed again
    - SPARC manual focus now properly updates the optical path when selecting
      the second camera
    - Allow spectrum acquisition with an exposure time < 10 ms
    - Zeiss driver handles better long commands
    - AR spectral plugin: warn if acquisition tab not selected
    - AR spectral plugin: better acquisition time estimate on slow camera readout
    - Persitent data was not saved if /etc/odemis-settings.yaml was not present
    - At start-up, the semcomedi driver would sometimes report a non-square pixel size
    - Fix andorcam2 driver error handler causing a bigger error
    - Reduce SPARC live update frequency to 0.5 Hz.
    - Delay PMT protection a tiny bit after end of acquisition
    - Fix regression preventing loading AR background containing multiple AR images
    - Fix Fluorescence stream ordering when emission is the same between two streams
    - Fix the year in filename sometimes replaced by %Y
    - Fix hamamatsurx driver incorrectly logging an error at init with Python 3
    - After SPARC manual focus, immediately pause the stream, to keep the slit image
    - Fix font dialog selection sometimes appearing on Windows
    - Fix import of greyscale TIFF in the merge RGB plugin
    - Fix bug reporter sending corrupted attachements
    - Command line utils also use Python 3 by default
    - AR spectral plugin could display the wavelength inverted on some systems
    - Do not fail after temporal spectral acquisition for a display error
    - Fix icon background in the Windows Viewer
    - Fix DELPHI calibration window on Python 3
    - Fix cli_rgb plugin not using the correct filter
    - Fix file selection in plugin with no specific file pattern
    - Fix overview thumbnail not always updated (DELPHI)
    - Fix logging of fine alignment scaling_xy (SECOM)
    - Fix reading/writing streakcam calibration on Python 3
    - Fix npmc driver not starting on Python 3
    - The default python interpreter is Python 3
    - Update tescan driver to use the latest library, compatible with Python 3
    - Automatically close DELPHI first calibration dialog when sample is ejected
    - CL intensity streams are shown using the same blending mode as for FM

